    "synthesis_hints": [
      "The EPYC 9224 has only 4 active CCDs (24 cores \u00f7 6 cores per CCD). Lower-CCD-count Genoa parts are GMI3-fabric-limited to ~110-150 GB/s of realized bandwidth regardless of channel population. So 8-channel (8x32GB) vs 4-channel (4x64GB) is roughly 10-15% bandwidth difference, not 50%. Surface this tradeoff when 4x64GB is meaningfully cheaper.\n",
      "Watch for Kingston \"E\" suffix \u2014 that's UDIMM, not RDIMM. HPE / Dell / Cisco \"SmartMemory\" branded modules carry custom SPD firmware and may not POST on the H13SSL-NT.\n"
    ]
  },
